9. Discussion: Limitations, Conjectures, and Future Work

9.1 Conjectures and Open Problems

Conjecture 2 (Probabilistic Error Bound). Under the invariant measure $\mu$ of the system, the local surrogate error satisfies

\mathbb{P}_{\mathbf{x} \sim \mu} \left( \|\Phi_h(\mathbf{x}) - \text{GraphTNI}_\theta(\mathbf{x})\| > \epsilon \right) \le \delta,

where $\delta$ decays exponentially with the training set size. This would justify that high-error states (e.g., close encounters) are rare.

Conjecture 3 (Distribution Exit Time). For a training distribution covering a ball of radius $R$ around the initial state, the expected time until the trajectory exits this ball under pure GraphTNI rollout satisfies

\mathbb{E}[t_{\text{exit}}] \ge \frac{1}{\bar{\lambda}} \ln\!\left( \frac{R}{\epsilon_{\text{LLM}}} \right),

where $\bar{\lambda}$ is the time-averaged local Lyapunov exponent. This provides a theoretical safe horizon for surrogate-only rollout.

9.2 Failure Modes and Mitigations

